  {
    "op": "replace",
    "path": "/table_schemas/authorization_use_events/invariants",
    "value": [
      "ACTIVATED is the first event for an authorization; REQUEST_RESERVED is the only reservation state",
      "there is no generic RESERVED state",
      "event ordinals are gapless per authorization and rows are immutable",
      "spec_revision equals governing replay revision 23",
      "missing/partial evidence cannot satisfy REQUEST_RESERVATION_CANCELLED_NO_START or continuation eligibility",
      "REQUEST_START_CONFIRMED and REQUEST_START_AMBIGUOUS capture_start_event_row_sha256 resolves to a STARTED capture row",
      "REQUEST_TERMINAL_RECORDED capture_terminal_event_row_sha256 resolves to the matching INTERRUPTED or COMPLETED capture row",
      "authorization_id, authorization_record_file_sha256, authorized_request_set_file_sha256, reservation_id, request_id, execution_ordinal, and attempt_number are identical across each authorization-use event and its bound capture row",
      "REQUEST_RESERVATION_CANCELLED_NO_START capture_audit_snapshot_sha256 covers the complete reservation interval and proves zero matching STARTED and terminal rows",
      "process launch is durably permitted only after a committed STARTED capture row; therefore a complete zero-STARTED snapshot is positive no-launch evidence"
